If a header is against the pushrod tube, won't it heat the oil draining 
back through there, since there is no heaterbox to flush the heat? I'd 
try to put a heat-proof thermal break in between.

Courtney Hook wrote:
I had to clearance a pushrod tube very gently by about 1/8" to
